# Playwright E2E Standards

## Testing philosophy

- **Test user-visible behavior.** Verify what end users see and interact with. Avoid implementation details (CSS classes, internal state, function names).
- **Isolate tests.** Each test must run independently with its own storage, cookies, and data. Use `beforeEach` for shared setup (e.g. login). Use [setup project](https://playwright.dev/docs/auth) for shared signed-in state.
- **Avoid third-party dependencies.** Don't test external sites or APIs you don't control. Mock with `page.route()` or `context.route()`.
- **Control data.** Use staging with stable data, or seed fixtures. For visual regression, keep OS and browser versions consistent.

## Locators

### Priority order

1. `getByRole()` — accessibility role + name (preferred).
2. `getByLabel()` — form controls.
3. `getByText()` — static content.
4. `getByPlaceholder()` — inputs.
5. `getByAltText()` — images.
6. `getByTitle()` — title attribute.
7. `getByTestId()` — fallback for dynamic/structural elements. Configure `testIdAttribute` in config if using custom attr (e.g. `data-pw`).

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' });
page.getByLabel('Email').fill('user@example.com');
page.getByText('Welcome').first();

// ❌ BAD — fragile to DOM changes
page.locator('button.buttonIcon.episode-actions-later');
page.locator('#tsf div:nth-child(2) div.A8SBwf input');
```

### Chaining and filtering

```typescript
await page
  .getByRole('listitem')
  .filter({ hasText: 'Product 2' })
  .getByRole('button', { name: 'Add to cart' })
  .click();
```

### iframes

Use `page.frameLocator()` to target elements inside iframes. Built-in locators work inside `frameLocator`:

```typescript
await page.frameLocator('iframe[name="embed"]').getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' }).click();
```

### Use codegen

Run `npx playwright codegen <url>` or use the VS Code extension to generate resilient locators.

## Assertions

- **Use web-first assertions** that auto-wait and retry: `toBeVisible()`, `toHaveText()`, `toContainText()`, `toHaveValue()`, etc.
- **Always await** the `expect` call.
- **Never use manual checks** like `expect(await locator.isVisible()).toBe(true)` — they don't retry.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
await expect(page.getByText('Welcome')).toBeVisible();
await expect(page.getByTestId('status')).toHaveText('Submitted');

// ❌ BAD
expect(await page.getByText('Welcome').isVisible()).toBe(true);
```

- **Soft assertions** for multiple checks that shouldn't stop the test immediately:
  `await expect.soft(locator).toHaveText('Success');`
- **Custom expect messages** for clarity: `await expect(locator, 'should show success').toBeVisible();`
- **Async polling**: Use `expect.poll()` or `expect().toPass()` for conditions that need retries (e.g. API eventually returns 200).

## Actions

- Prefer `fill()` over `type()` for inputs — faster and replaces existing value.
- Use `press()` for keyboard shortcuts (Enter, Tab, Escape).
- Use `check()` / `uncheck()` for checkboxes and radio buttons.

## Test structure

### One feature per test

Each test should verify one user flow. Short, focused tests make failures easy to interpret.

### Page Object Model (POM)

Extract page logic for complex flows:

```typescript
// pages/LoginPage.ts
export class LoginPage {
  constructor(private page: Page) {}
  async login(email: string, password: string) {
    await this.page.getByLabel('Email').fill(email);
    await this.page.getByLabel('Password').fill(password);
    await this.page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Sign in' }).click();
  }
}
```

### Hooks

- Use `test.beforeEach` for per-test setup (e.g. goto, login).
- Use `test.describe` to group related tests.
- Use `test.describe.configure({ mode: 'parallel' })` when tests in a file are independent.

### Fixtures

- Prefer **fixtures** over beforeEach for setup+teardown. Use `test.extend()` to create custom fixtures (e.g. `todoPage`, `loggedInPage`).
- Built-in: `page`, `context`, `browser`, `request`. Use `request` for API calls.
- Worker-scoped fixtures (`{ scope: 'worker' }`) for shared setup (e.g. one account per worker).
- Encapsulate setup and teardown in the same fixture with `await use(value)`.

### test.step

Use `test.step()` for logical steps in reports and traces:

```typescript
await test.step('fill login form', async () => {
  await page.getByLabel('Email').fill('user@example.com');
  await page.getByLabel('Password').fill('secret');
});
```

## Network and mocking

- Mock third-party APIs and external services with `page.route()` or `context.route()`.
- Use `route.fulfill()` to return controlled responses.

```typescript
await page.route('**/api/fetch_external', route =>
  route.fulfill({ status: 200, body: JSON.stringify(testData) })
);
await page.goto('/dashboard');
```

## File structure

```
e2e/  (or tests/)
├── fixtures/              # Custom test.extend fixtures
├── pages/                 # Page Object classes
├── tests/
│   ├── auth.setup.ts      # Setup project for auth
│   ├── auth.spec.ts
│   └── dashboard.spec.ts
├── playwright/
│   └── .auth/             # Storage state (add to .gitignore)
├── playwright.config.ts
└── global-setup.ts        # Optional: one-time setup
```

## API testing

- Use the built-in `request` fixture for API tests. No browser needed.
- Prepare server state via API before UI tests: create data, then `page.goto()`.
- Validate postconditions via API after UI actions.
- Set `baseURL` and `extraHTTPHeaders` in config for API requests.

```typescript
test('created issue appears in list', async ({ request, page }) => {
  await request.post('/api/issues', { data: { title: 'Bug 1' } });
  await page.goto('/issues');
  await expect(page.getByText('Bug 1')).toBeVisible();
});
```

## Authentication

- Use a **setup project** with `testMatch: /.*\.setup\.ts/` to authenticate once; save `storageState` to `playwright/.auth/`.
- Add `playwright/.auth/` to `.gitignore` — it contains sensitive cookies.
- Other projects depend on setup and use `storageState: 'playwright/.auth/user.json'`.
- Authenticate via API when supported — faster than UI login.
- For tests that modify server state: use one account per worker (worker-scoped auth fixture).

## Config (`playwright.config.ts`)

- Use TypeScript (`.ts`) for better IDE support.
- Define **projects** for browsers: Chromium, Firefox, WebKit (at least Chromium for CI).
- Set `retries` (e.g. 1) for CI to handle flakiness.
- Configure `trace: 'on-first-retry'` for failed test traces; avoid `'on'` for every run.
- Set `baseURL` for `page.goto('/path')` shortcuts.
- Use `use.video` or `use.trace` for failure debugging.
- **Timeouts**: Set `timeout` (test), `expect.timeout`, or per-test `test.setTimeout()`. Default test timeout is 30s.
